  "text": "Signals received from the environment are communicated via the input pathway to the main pacemaker. These signals, named zeitgebers or timing cues, are used to synchronize the pacemaker oscillations with the solar day-night cycle. Light is consequently the strongest zeitgeber, but also temperature, noise, food, exercise and melatonin can act as zeitgebers [CITATION_1] .",
